      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">LADIES' ¶ LEICHARDT ¶ SEARCH COMMITTEE ¶ Upper Darling ¶ 5. May 1865....</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">65.05.05</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Duncan McIntyre</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">M65/4706, unit 209, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS transcribed by a clerk with 'Signed Duncan M'Intyre' in M's hand.</p>
               </note>
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">LADIES'</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">LEICHARDT</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">SEARCH COMMITTEE</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Upper Darling<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">NSW.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">5. May 1865.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr. Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have just heard that there has been heavy rain at Mt. Murchison<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Sheep station on the Darling River, near present day Wilcannia.</p>
               </note> and all along the Darling and to the northward, so that, there will be no difficulty about water for the next two or three months.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will be back at Mt. Murchison in a month or two for a mob of Horses, I will then start, direct for the Flinders.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Flinders River, north Qld.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Should the Expedition be ready to start then we could all go together, as I know all the watering places. It would save the leader a good deal of trouble. I will have about a hundred Horses to take over. I expect to overtake the other stock about the Thompson or head of the Flinders, I will then leave what Horses I do not require and go on to select a Run somewhere on the Leichhardt River.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Should I be appointed leader everything would require to be at Mt. Murchison in July at furthest, As I shall be away for good by that time. That is Camel waterbags &amp; Camel pack saddles and anything else that might be required such as Mt. Barometer<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Mountain barometer, used for determining elevations.</p>
               </note> or Berlin water Apparatus<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Hypsometer, used for determining elevations by measuring the temperature at which water boils.</p>
               </note> or both.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Nautical Almanacs<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Published by the Greenwich Observatory, with tables for determining longitude.</p>
               </note> for this and the next two or three years, a few Navy Colts Revolvers and 20 boxes revolv. caps.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Camel Hobbles</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>24 pair Stirrup leathers.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>There is no paddock at Mt. Murchison or in the neighborhood</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>There should be an account of everything Leichhardt had with him — given to whoever is going to search for him, such as the number of Horses, Cattle, Mules, sheep, Goats etc. etc. white men and natives.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You can address anything to me</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Kallara</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Darling River, N.S.W.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Signed</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Duncan M'Intyre<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The President of the Ladies' Leichardt Search Committee, Eliza Bromby, forwarded this letter to the Chief Secretary, J. McCulloch, on 22 May 1865. Her covering letter explained that the Ladies' Leichhardt Search Committee was 'anxious with as little delay as possible to ascertain how soon they will be authorized in entering into negotiations with the leader whose services they desire to secure for their proposed expedition. A steadily increasing interest in the cause gives every hope of ultimate success.' On 26 May McCulloch minuted: 'Th Wright to see me on Monday'. On 29 May he minuted: 'If the<seg style="font-weight: bold; "> </seg>3 other Colonies give £500 each.'</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also M to J. McCulloch, 29 May 1865.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
